# Orange France DHCP authentication credentials.
# Format: USERNAME:PASSWORD on a single line, no spaces, no quotes.
# Username is usually fti/<id>; password is provided by Orange (paper documentation or Orange app).
# This file must be owned by root and chmod 600.
#
# Copy to /etc/orange-auth on the OpenWrt router. The orange-gen-auth.sh script reads it
# to generate fresh DHCP Option 90 (and DHCPv6 Option 11) RFC 3118 authentication blobs.
#
# Example:
fti/abc1234:replace-with-actual-password
